Description: client-matched virtual displays for Sunshine/Apollo on KDE Wayland
 Proteo creates a virtual display at the exact resolution and refresh rate a
 Moonlight client requests when a Sunshine/Apollo stream starts, makes it the
 stream target, and restores the physical monitor configuration when the
 stream ends — including automatically on host crash, holder death, suspend
 and shutdown (proteo-guard failsafe daemon).
 .
 It hooks into the streaming host via the stable global_prep_cmd interface
 and SUNSHINE_CLIENT_* environment variables: no fork, no patches. Targets
 KDE Plasma 6 on Wayland (KWin output management) with EVDI virtual outputs.
